title: All of Kate Middleton's Alexander McQueen outfits - from her iconic wedding dress to her stunning BAFTAs gown
text: All of Kate Middleton's Alexander McQueen outfits - from her iconic wedding dress to her stunning BAFTAs gown The Duchess of Cambridge's love for the British brand dates back to her wedding, when she wore a stunning lace and satin bridal dress designed by Sarah Burton. We look back on all of Kate's Alexander McQueen outfits since 2011 Share By Danielle Stacey 09:00, 18 FEB 2017 In a bardot style tiered number for the BAFTAs in February 2017 (Photo: Rex Features) 1 of 30 A patriotic poppy dress to meet with Olympic and Paralympic medallists in October 2016 (Photo: PA) 2 of 30 A red and white ruffled frock to greet the crowds in Vancouver on the royal tour of Canada in September 2016 (Photo: FilmMagic) 3 of 30 Kate watched Andy Murray win the men's Wimbledon final in July 2016 in a printed shift dress (Photo: Glyn Kirk/ AFP/Getty) 4 of 30 Kate recycled a cream boat neck coat dress for the Trooping of the Colour to mark the Queen's 90th birthday in June 2016 (Photo: Anwar Hussein/WireImage) 5 of 30 Kate recycled her ruffled cream coat dress from Prince George's christening in 2013, for a garden party in May 2016 (Photo: Getty) 6 of 30 We saw Kate wear this military-style blouse and skirt for a second time for a visit to Portsmouth, in May 2016 (Photo: David Sims/WENN) 7 of 30 The Duchess departed Bhutan in a white broderie anglaise dress designed by Sarah Burton for Alexander McQueen in May 2016 (Photo: Heathcliff O'Malley-Pool/Getty Images) 8 of 30 Kate arrives in India in a red printed peplum number in April 2016 (Photo: Splash) 9 of 30 The third time we've seen Kate in this red peplum detail and pleated skirt dress, for the Anna Freud charity Christmas party in December 2015 (Photo: Rex Features) 10 of 30 The first time we saw Kate in the cream McQueen coat dress for Princess Charlotte's Christening in July 2015 - she later wore it to the Trooping of the Colour in 2016 (Photo: Chris Jackson/AFP/Getty) 11 of 30 Kate looked lovely during her second pregnancy in this pale pink McQueen coat for the Commonwealth Observance service in May 2015 12 of 30 The Duchess wore this military-style ensemble for a visit to Bletchley Park in June 2014 (Photo: Splash News) 13 of 30 A light blue/grey skirt suit for the Trooping of the Colour in 2014 (Photo: Zed Jameson/FameFlynet) 14 of 30 In a peach lace McQueen dress for a garden party at Buckingham Palace in 2014 - the second time we saw the Duchess in it (Photo: REUTERS) 15 of 30 A bespoke cornflower blue coat with pretty pleating on the back and blue suede pumps - also from McQueen - for a wreath-laying ceremony in New Zealand in 2014 (Photo: Getty) 16 of 30 Stepping off the plane in Adelaide on the Austalia tour in 2014 in a pretty pastel pink skirted dress (Photo: Daniel Kalisz/Getty Images) 17 of 30 A dove grey coat dress for Easter Sunday Service during the royal tour of Australia in 2014 (Photo: Getty) 18 of 30 Kate wearing her favourite McQueen red dress for a Dramatic Arts reception in 2014 (Photo: Rex) 19 of 30 Kate wearing a cream Alexander McQueen coat dress for Prince George's christening (Photo: Getty) 20 of 30 Kate stunned in a white and gold floor-length gown for a dinner hosted by the King of Malaysia, at the King's Istana, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia (Photo: Getty) 21 of 30 A white broderie anglaise suit in Singapore for William and Kateâ€™s Diamond Jubilee Tour to the South Pacific and Far East in 2012 (Photo: Rex Features) 22 of 30 The first time we saw Kate in the peach lace number for the Jubilee service in 2012 (Photo: Getty) 23 of 30 The first time we saw the red wool crepe dress for the Jubilee River Pageant in 2012 (Photo: 2012 Getty Images) 24 of 30 Possibly Kate's sexiest McQueen dress. She wore this strapless velvet number to the Military Awards in 2011 (Photo: Getty) 25 of 30 Kate stole the limelight from the A-listers for the BAFTA Brits To Watch event in 2011 (Photo: Getty) 26 of 30 In a sailor-esque outfit for a visit to Province House on the America and Canada tour in 2011 (Photo: 2011 Getty Images) 27 of 30 A military-style jacket dress for Armed Forces Day in 2011 (Photo: Getty) 28 of 30 Newly-wed Kate attended her first Trooping the Colour parade in 2011 in a white McQueen coat dress (Photo: Getty) 29 of 30 Kate blew the world away in her long-sleeved lace and satin gown designed by Sarah Burton for McQueen on her wedding day in April 2011 (Photo: Getty Images) 30 of 30 More On Kate Middleton, Duchess of Cambridge
